activateRegistration(uint256).details: Activates the service and its sensitive components.

params.agentParams: Number of agent instances and required bond to register an instance in the service.
params.configHash: IPFS hash pointing to the config metadata.
params.serviceOwner: Individual that creates and controls a service.
params.threshold: Threshold for a multisig composed by agents.
params.token: ERC20 token address for the security deposit, or ETH.

deploy(uint256,address,bytes).details: Creates multisig instance controlled by the set of service agent instances and deploys the service.

params.data: Data payload for the multisig creation.

getOperatorRegisterAgentsNonce(address,u.details: Gets the (operator | service Id) nonce for the register agents message data.

getOperatorUnbondNonce(address,uint256).details: Gets the (operator | service Id) nonce for the unbond message data.

getRegisterAgentsHash(address,address,ui.details: Gets the register agents message hash for the operator.

params.agentIds: Agent Ids corresponding to each agent instance address.
params.agentInstances: Agent instance addresses operator is going to register.
params.nonce: Nonce for the register agents message from the pair of (operator | service Id).

getUnbondHash(address,address,uint256,ui.details: Gets the unbond message hash for the operator.

params.nonce: Nonce for the unbond message from the pair of (operator | service Id).

isOperatorHashApproved(address,bytes32).details: Checks if the hash provided by the operator is approved.

returns._0: True, if the hash provided by the operator is approved.

operatorApproveHash(bytes32).details: Approves message hash for the operator address.

params.agentIds: Canonical Ids of the agent correspondent to the agent instance.

registerAgentsWithSignature(address,uint.details: Registers agent instances of the operator by the service owner via the operator's pre-signed message hash.

params.agentIds: Canonical Ids of the agent correspondent to the agent instance.
params.operator: Operator address that signed the register agents message hash.
params.signature: Signature byte array associated with operator message hash signature.

returns.success: True, if the the function executed successfully.

setIdentityRegistryBridger(address).details: Sets identity registry bridger contract address.

params.newIdentityRegistryBridger: New identity registry bridger contract address.

setOperatorWhitelist(address).details: Sets the operator whitelist contract address.

unbond(uint256).details: Unbonds agent instances of the operator from the service.

returns.refund: The amount of refund returned to the operator.

unbondWithSignature(address,uint256,byte.details: Unbonds agent instances of the operator by the service owner via the operator's pre-signed message hash.

params.operator: Operator address that signed the unbond message hash.
params.signature: Signature byte array associated with operator message hash signature.

returns.refund: The amount of refund returned to the operator.
returns.success: True, if the function executed successfully.

update(address,bytes32,uint32[],(uint32,.details: Updates a service in a CRUD way.

params.agentParams: Number of agent instances and required bond to register an instance in the service.
params.configHash: IPFS hash pointing to the config metadata.
params.threshold: Threshold for a multisig composed by agents.
params.token: ERC20 token address for the security deposit, or ETH.

changeImplementation(address).notice: Make sure implementation contract has function to change its implementation.

registerAgentsWithSignature(address,uint.notice: Note that this function accounts for the operator being the EOA, or the contract that has an         isValidSignature() function that would confirm the message hash was signed by the operator contract.         Otherwise, if the message hash has been pre-approved, the corresponding map of hashes is going to         to verify the signed hash, similar to the Safe contract implementation in v1.3.0:         https://github.com/safe-global/safe-contracts/blob/186a21a74b327f17fc41217a927dea7064f74604/contracts/GnosisSafe.sol#L240-L304         Also note that only the service owner is able to call this function on behalf of the operator.

unbondWithSignature(address,uint256,byte.notice: Note that this function accounts for the operator being the EOA, or the contract that has an         isValidSignature() function that would confirm the message hash was signed by the operator contract.         Otherwise, if the message hash has been pre-approved, the corresponding map of hashes is going to         to verify the signed hash, similar to the Safe contract implementation in v1.3.0:         https://github.com/safe-global/safe-contracts/blob/186a21a74b327f17fc41217a927dea7064f74604/contracts/GnosisSafe.sol#L240-L304         Also note that only the service owner is able to call this function on behalf of the operator.
